As already stated, this is a Safe-class SCP.

Additionally:



Tests are to be run only in Site-76's specially constructed testing environment for SCP-281, with special care being taken not to introduce foreign organisms. Should such an organism inadvertently be present during activation of SCP-281, personnel overseeing testing are to start the chamber's incineration sequence.
附加记录：    

So bacteria are a problem with this thing. That makes sense, but you don't tell us to keep this thing itself sterile. No decontamination of the device prior to or following use. Just that we test it in a  It would help to state it's a clean room, everything going in and coming out has to be decontaminated, etc., rather than implying it by telling people not to let any foreign organisms in, and to clarify that the device itself must be kept sterile.

The  contingency is not bad in and of itself, but with the minimal attention that's given to telling people how to avoid it, it seems a wonder this thing isn't a pile of slag by now.

Then there's this:



D-Class personnel used in testing are not to be informed on the nature of SCP-281.
附加记录：    

We test this on people because we apparently just wanna watch them wither away, instead of lab rats or guinea pigs or what have you, and ignore the fact that people are distinctly not sterile. Nor is most any living thing, but a rat bred and grown in a controlled environment would be distinctly more so than a person. Also easier to replace.



and a [REDACTED]. Though incongruent, this last component is believed to be the primary source of SCP-281's anomalous properties.
附加记录：    

This is a pretty lame redaction and doesn't add anything. This is a cop out to blackbox how the SCP functions. I don't mean paste ████ over it, though it does that. I mean that it clumsily obfuscates how it functions, which is pointless, since you go on to say that despite our belief for some unknown reason this component is the source of the timefuck, we still can't replicate the effect despite presumably being able to duplicate it in full. And that's fine. But it raises questions as to why we think this component is somehow integral to its anomalous function, any more so than any other part, when we have no apparent evidence of this fact besides its  While this incongruity may certainly be strange and worthy of note, that in and of itself isn't enough to assume it's what makes the SCP function anomalously.

The only way I can think of to conclusively test that assertion is to disassemble the device and reassemble it, substituting copies of parts for all but the supposedly incongruent one, such that it's the only part from the original employed in the copy. If the copy demonstrates the same effects, we've got a winner, and we can safely classify this single component as the SCP. This would be even safer than storing the Timefuck T-1000 powered in a locker1, as it needs power to run, an isolated component can't do anything on its own, and anyone intending to use it for testing or nefarious purposes would need to assemble it first.

Lastly, the addendum feels like it's trying far too hard to inflate this thing's importance.

Footnotes
1. Which is pretty stupid, as you don't generally store guns loaded, nor bombs fused and active.








